definition: dozen
one/1/single/a (article)/as soon as/entire/whole/all/throughout/"one" radical in Chinese characters (Kangxi radical 1)/also pr. [yao1] for greater clarity when spelling out numbers digit by digit
to beat/to strike/to hit/to break/to type/to mix up/to build/to fight/to fetch/to make/to tie up/to issue/to shoot/to calculate/to play (a game)/since/from
dozen (loanword)

sentences.english: There are 237 more; a dozen or so are positive.
sentences.chinese: 还有237个评论，一打左右是夸奖的。

sentences.english: My mother bought a dozen eggs.
John had sent me a dozen white roses to mark my first- year teaching.
sentences.chinese: 约翰送给我一打白玫瑰，庆祝我第一年的教学工作。

sentences.english: There are no less than a dozen of such low lives on this CNN forum.
sentences.chinese: 在CNN论坛上就有不少于一打这么多的五毛党。

sentences.english: He went over to his roll of bedding and drew out a writing pad.
sentences.chinese: 他走到他的展盖卷，拿出一打书写纸。

sentences.english: When the fight begin, he think it politic to leave.
sentences.chinese: 刚一打起来他就想到还是走为上策。

sentences.english: On the countertop, add a neat stack of new white towels and scented reeds.
sentences.chinese: 在梳妆台面上，加上一打整洁的新白毛巾和芳香棒儿。

sentences.english: You can't get through a show without seeing maybe a dozen different commercials.
sentences.chinese: 你看一部剧能看到大概一打不同的广告。

sentences.english: Jenny was with child when she left Guangzhou.
sentences.chinese: 刚一打起来他就想到还是走为上策。

sentences.english: There are probably about a dozen small nicks total on the 24 edge lines that form the two cabinets.
sentences.chinese: 大概有一打就24边缘线，形成了两箱共小尼克斯。

sentences.english: He is such a three-bottle man that he can drink a dozen beers straight.
sentences.chinese: 他能够一口气喝完一打啤酒，真是个能喝酒的人。

sentences.english: Call up thefloristandtell him to send my wife a dozen roses.
sentences.chinese: 打个电话给花商，请他送一打玫瑰给我太太。

sentences.english: The next morning the barber found a dozen lawyers waiting for a free haircut.
sentences.chinese: 第二天，理发师发现门前站了一打律师等着免费理发。

sentences.english: Those online critics, they’re a dime a dozen.
sentences.chinese: 那些网上所谓的批评家，不值钱到一毛钱就能买一打。
